album.name: So Romantic - EP

annotations:
Carl Jung was a Swiss psychiatrist and psychoanalyst who founded analytical psychology. Jung believed that the human psyche, or the body, mind and soul, was made up of three parts—the ego, the personal unconscious and the collective unconscious.

Buckley is referring possibly to a poster of one of Jungs book covers he has hanging on the wall.

Similar to the individual Buckley sang about in the first verse of the song who took ayahuasca, this person is also looking to be connected to a higher understanding of human consciousness.

In this context the shaman is the individual responsible for leading the ayahuasca ceremony.

Ayahuasca is often used to help people open their minds to a higher level of understanding of themselves and the people around them. Buckley is referring to the idea that we are on our own spiritual paths and even a truly enlightened Shaman cannot predict the future for her and her lover.

Ayahuasca is a plant based psychedelic drug made from boiling the leaves of the Banisteriopsis caapi vine. It’s consumed in liquid form. Ayahuasca has been used for centuries by First Nations peoples from contemporary Peru, Brazil, Colombia and Ecuador for religious ritual and therapeutic purposes.

Ayahuasca has become popular with white Americans who travel to Peru – like the lover Buckley is singing about – to experience the spiritual enlightenment the drug is reported to reveal.
